        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        German Chancellor Friedrich Merz navigated a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-jun-25-spotlights-h1-1-40-minute-meeting" target="_blank">40-minute meeting</a> with Trump in the Oval Office without falling victim to the public humiliation. Merz reminded the US President that both countries should put more pressure on Russia to end its war in Ukraine. Merz referenced <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-jun-25-spotlights-h1-2-d-day" target="_blank">D-Day</a>, when the Americans invaded Europe to halt the war in Europe in 1944. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      Merz also attempted to persuade Trump to resolve the tariffs. Trump confirmed that he wants to have a good relationship, adding that any trade agreement would also be up to the EU. A 10% tariff on EU imports is in place until the July deadline, except for cars, which have a 25% tariff, and steel and aluminum, which have seen their tariff doubled to 50%.</p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Merz gifted Trump a framed birth certificate of his German grandfather, Friedrich Trump. This meeting set a positive precedent for future discussions. This is especially important in the lead-up to the G7 and NATO summits.</p>
