        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-top:4px;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>ðŸ‡¨ðŸ‡³ China - Helps Russia.</strong> Russia is closing the drone gap with Ukraine, aided by covert Chinese tech support despite official denials. Ukrainian officials claim that China provides key components through shell companies. While Ukraine pioneered drone warfare, Russia outproduces it, making 300 long-range drones daily (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-jun-25-analysis-h2-6-drone-wars" target="_blank">drone wars</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>ðŸ‡­ðŸ‡º Hungary - EU rules against it.</strong> The EUâ€™s top court has declared that Hungaryâ€™s ban on LGBTQ+ content in schools and on TV violates human rights. Advocate General Tamara Ä†apeta said the law spreads harm, not protection, especially to LGBTQ+ minors. The law, passed in 2021, stigmatizes LGBTQ+ lives and breaches EU rights on dignity, non-discrimination, and media liberty (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-jun-25-analysis-h2-7-about-the-ruling" target="_blank">about the ruling</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>ðŸ‡ªðŸ‡º European Union - Sounds alarm to China.</strong> The EU is urging China to ease export restrictions on rare earth materials, which are essential for industries such as automotive and electronics. The EU calls for a more efficient licensing system, while US officials express growing frustration over delays (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-jun-25-analysis-h2-8-export-controls" target="_blank">export controls</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>ðŸ‡ªðŸ‡¬ Egypt - Vows to protect.</strong> 
           Egypt pledges to preserve Saint Catherine's Monastery following a court ruling that declared the land to be public property. The court upheld the monksâ€™ right to use the monastery, easing fears of state seizure. Egypt is assuring Greece that it will maintain the site's religious value and continue cooperation to protect its judicial status (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-jun-25-analysis-h2-9-promises-made" target="_blank">promises made</a>).  
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>ðŸ‡»ðŸ‡³ Vietnam - Canceling 2-child policy.</strong> 
            Vietnam has scrapped its two-child policy to address declining birth percentage and an ageing population. However, many families remain reluctant to have more children due to rising living expenses, lack of time, and changing values. Citizens say they prioritize monetary stability and personal well-being over rearing babies (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-jun-25-analysis-h2-10-fewer-babies" target="_blank">fewer babies</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>ðŸ‡®ðŸ‡± Israel - Gaza arms.</strong> 
            PM Benjamin Netanyahu confirms that he is arming a clan in Gaza opposed to Hamas. Critics say the oppositional group, Abu Shabab, could further destabilize the region. The PM asserts this is helping Israeli soldiers, but opposition leaders say this is endangering national security, especially since this bypasses approval from other cabinet members (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-jun-25-analysis-h2-11-about-the-scandal" target="_blank">about the scandal</a>).
